added.title: The Scoop
added.description: The Titans find it odd when Starfire becomes friends with an ice cream scoop.

added.title: The Real Orangins!
added.description: Robin tries again to tell the real origin story of the Teen Titans.

added.title: The Metric System vs. Freedom
added.description: Robin teaches the other Titans about the difference between the Imperial System and the Metric System.

added.title: The Demon
added.description: Chloe and Ice Bear accidentally lose Chloe's prized hoodie to the ferocious dog next store. They go on a mission to get it back.

added.title: The Fair
added.description: The Baby Bears make a deal with a carnival worker to be prizes for a game of ball toss.

added.title: Road Trip
added.description: Chloe and the Bears take a road trip to see a meteor shower. Ice Bear, the only one licensed to drive, is put in charge, which becomes harder than he thought.

added.title: Spa Day
added.description: The Bears have a relaxing day at the spa. Grizz tries to get everything the spa has to offer. Panda gets trapped in the steam room with an old man. And Ice Bear plays ping pong.

added.title: Teacher's Pet
added.description: The Baby Bears escape their hectic lives by attending school.

added.title: The Line
added.description: The family has waited in line outside the movie theater all night. They are devastated when Larry tells them they won't get into the first screening of the Stellar Odyssey sequel. But, hardcore fans that they are, the Wattersons are determined to be the first to see the movie and so set about battling their way to the front of the queue.

added.title: The Law
added.description: Donut Cop shows Gumball and Darwin that the smallest misdemeanour can lead to a breakdown in law.  Gumball jaywalks and is pulled over by Donut Cop. When Gumball objects he is told that even the smallest misdemeanor can lead to a breakdown in law. In an effort to impress the kids Donut Cop takes them for a ride-along in his cop car and gets carried away, progressively breaking the law himself. He soon proves that the tiniest offense can indeed snowball into complete lawlessness!

added.title: The Lesson
added.description: Gumball and Darwin get put in detention and quickly find it's more like prison than school. And there's only one thing to do in prison... ESCAPE!

added.title: The Limit
added.description: The Watterson family faces Mom's wrath in a supermarket.

added.title: The Laziest
added.description: Gumball and Darwin challenge Dad to a "lazy-off."

added.title: Roundabout Part 1
added.description: Forever Knight finally assembles his Round Table of young but super-powerful Knights, including— Ben?! With Ben's help, Forever Knight leads his new minions in an all-out attack on a Particle Accelerator - his true intention to transform it into a Time Machine and conquer history!

added.title: Forever Road
added.description: During a drag race, Ben hopes to stay neck and neck with Vin Ethanol and La Grange as XLR8, but when his watch keeps shorting out, our hero must get creative if he is to keep up with his fast and furious foes!

added.title: Prey or Play
added.description: After receiving a super-exclusive ticket to Adrenaland, Ben leaves behind Grandpa Max and Gwen to enjoy the perks of being the parks only attendant, but when he learns he's not alone, our hero must now contend with the only kid who could afford the price of admission: Billy Billions!

added.title: The Night Ben Tennyson Came to Town
added.description: Team Tennyson travels to Wheeler, "the liveliest mining town on Route 66", but when Ben becomes paranoid that the Forever Knight is out to get him, he must try to convince his fam while also stopping his new foe from destroying the town.

added.title: Fear in the Family
added.description: Ben and Gwen can't wait for the Omni-Copter to arrive at the Great Pyramids, but when bad weather disrupts their flight, they soon come face-to-face with The Fogg and its spawn: The Fogg Family!

added.title: Power Punchers
added.description: Fed up with losing in video games to his Dad, Craig seeks training in the Creek.

added.title: Creek Cart Racers
added.description: A high-speed race with a high-stakes prize may be too much for Craig and his friends.

added.title: Secret Book Club
added.description: Kelsey starts a super secret book club to introduce Craig and JP to the joys of reading.

added.title: Sausage and Sweetie Smash
added.description: Apple and Onion must conquer their obsessions of sausages and a video game.

added.title: Selfish Shellfish
added.description: Apple and Onion have to prove that they're not selfish when they do their good deeds.

added.title: The Music Store Thief
added.description: Apple and Onion have to defend the music store from instrument theft to get a key to the store.

added.title: The Fly
added.description: Apple and Onion must rid their apartment of a fly or face eviction.

added.title: The Inbetween
added.description: Apple and Onion get lost beneath their floorboards and must find a way out.

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems get a chance to catch up when they're all snowed in together.

added.title: Why So Blue?
added.description: Steven has heard rumors of a pair of Gems that are still destroying worlds. If he can't stop them, maybe Lapis can.

added.title: Aluxes
added.description: When Vic finds an ancient relic that summons a gang of mischievous creatures, he uses them to do his bidding, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: Guillermo's Gathering
added.description: When Vic & Val are forced to go to Guillermo's boring birthday party, they devise a scheme to leave early, but end up discovering that the party is way cooler than they thought.

added.title: Balloon Boys
added.description: Vic & Val go on a hot air balloon trip with Sal and compete to be his favorite, but things go awry when they try to use the magical Nazca Lines to their advantage.

added.title: The Great Bongo Heist
added.description: The boys forget to get Chata a gift for Abuela Day and in a panicked move, they pretend that the bongo drums they borrowed from Xochi are for her. Knowing they have to return the drums, Victor & Valentino pretend to be burglars to steal the bongos back.

added.title: Escape From Bebe Bay
added.description: When Vic & Val accidentally turn themselves and Don into babies, they must escape a daycare center in order to change back to their normal ages.

added.title: Onion Trade
added.description: A boy trade between Steven and Onion escalates to epic proportions.

added.title: Monster Buddies
added.description: Steven accidentally releases a monster from a gem bubble and attempts to tame its wild, violent instincts.

added.title: Ocean Gem
added.description: The Ocean disappears on the first day of summer and Beach City is in a panic.

added.title: Marble Madness
added.description: Steven and the Gems encounter another droid from space.

added.title: Political Power
added.description: The Gems cause a power outage in Beach City, and Steven helps Mayor Dewey do damage control.

added.title: Badge-a-fire Explosion
added.description: When BC comes out of a rare state of hyper-focused creativity, he may have made something that could destroy all of PHV.

added.title: Zing Your Heart Out
added.description: When Adorabat starts to aggressively heckle everyone with her new zing power, she threatens the entire kingdom.

added.title: I Am a Sword
added.description: Finn starts having guilt nightmares about his missing Finn Sword but are the nightmares real?

added.title: Is That You?
added.description: After a memorial for a fallen ally, Jake starts acting very strange.

added.title: In Your Footsteps
added.description: A bear befriends Finn and Jake, but what are his true intentions?

added.title: Ignition Point
added.description: When Finn and Jake sneak into the Fire Kingdom, they get caught in the middle of a Flame family feud.

added.title: I Remember You
added.description: Ice King and Marceline share a tender and revealing few moments reminiscing.

added.title: Maellard's Package
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to wait at Maellard's mansion and get a very important delivery.

added.title: Marvolo the Wizard
added.description: Pops thinks that he's a wizard trapped in medieval times, and he wants to go back home.

added.title: The End of Muscle Man
added.description: The guys want to help Muscle Man finish his bucket list.

added.title: Sad Sax
added.description: Mordecai wants to get back together with C.J.

added.title: Party Horse
added.description: The guys want to help Party Horse pass his U.S. history test.

added.title: La Parisina
added.description: Cuando Starfire se obsesiona con una cuchara para servir helado, los demás intentan enseñarle que los objetos inanimados no pueden reemplazar a las personas.

added.title: Los Verdaderos Orijanes
added.description: Robin trata de contar la verdadera historia del origen de los Jóvenes Titanes.

added.title: El sistema metrico versus la libertad
added.description: Robin le enseña a los demás Titanes acerca de las diferencias entre el sistema imperial y el sistema métrico.

added.title: El demonio
added.description: Por accidente, Chloe y Polar pierden la chaqueta con capucha que tanto quiere Chloe en las garras del feroz perro de la tienda de al lado. Se embarcan en una misión para recuperarla.

added.title: La feria
added.description: Los Osos bebés hacen un trato con un empleado del parque de atracciones para convertirse en premios de un juego de lanzamiento de pelota.

added.title: El viaje
added.description: Chloe y los osos hacen un viaje en auto para ver una lluvia de meteoritos. Polar, el único que tiene licencia de conducir, está a cargo del manejo, lo cual se vuelve más difícil de lo que pensaba.

added.title: Dia de Spa
added.description: Los Osos se relajan en el spa. Grizz intenta usar todos los servicios del spa. Panda queda atrapado en la sala de vapor con un anciano. Y Polar juega al ping pong.

added.title: El Favorito de la Profesora
added.description: Los ositos van a la escuela para escapar de sus vidas agitadas.

added.title: Rodeo Parte 1
added.description: El Caballero por Siempre finalmente reúne a su Mesa Redonda de Caballeros jóvenes pero superpoderosos... i¿incluido Ben?! Con la ayuda de Ben, el Caballero lidera a sus nuevos súbditos en un ataque generalizado contra un acelerador de partículas.

added.title: Miedo en la Familia
added.description: Ben y Gwen están ansiosos por que el Omni-Copter llegue a las Grandes Pirámides. Pero cuando el mal tiempo interrumpe su vuelo, pronto se enfrentan cara a cara con Neblina y sus engendros: iLa familia Niebla!

added.title: Carretera por Siempre
added.description: Durante una carrera de aceleración, Ben espera mantenerse al mismo nivel con Vin Etanol y La Grange como XLR8. Pero cuando su reloj hace cortocircuito una y otra vez, nuestro héroe debe ser creativo si quiere seguir el ritmo de sus rápidos y furiosos enemigos.

added.title: Caza o Juego
added.description: Después de recibir un billete superexclusivo para Adrenalandia, Ben deja atrás al abuelo Max y a Gwen para disfrutar de las ventajas de ser el único asistente del parque. Pero pronto se entera de que no está solo.

added.title: La noche que Ben Tennyson vino al pueblo
added.description: El equipo Tennyson viaja a Wheeler, "la ciudad minera más animada de la Ruta 66". Pero cuando Ben se pone paranoico con la idea de que el Caballero por Siempre lo esté persiguiendo, debe tratar de convencer a su familia al mismo tiempo que evita que su nuevo enemigo destruya la ciudad.

added.title: Lord Vaquero Darrell
added.description: Todos se ven obligados a enfrentar grandes cambios en Boxmore.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Lord Cowboy Darrell
added.description: Everyone is forced to deal with some major changes at Boxmore.

added.title: Body Trouble
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Belly Bag have a disagreement, they separate and try to make each other jealous.

added.title: Festival de Cine en la Plaza
added.description: Cuando se organiza un festival de cine propio en la Plaza, iEnid y Rad están seguros de que su obra ganará!
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Plaza Film Festival
added.description: When the plaza has its own film festival, KO, Enid and Rad are sure their entry will win!

added.title: Veamos el Show de Boxmore
added.description: Nuestros héroes descubren que las grabaciones de la cámara de seguridad de Boxmore son la cosa más divertida del mundo.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Let's Watch the Boxmore Show
added.description: Our heroes discover that the Boxmore security camera feed is the most entertaining thing ever.

added.title: Bottom Bag
added.description: After receiving a new bag friend, Belly Bag has to realize its nefarious intentions to completely replace Belly Bag and stop it before it's too late.

added.title: Mystery Sleepover
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad attempt to solve a mystery.

added.title: Monster Party
added.description: Enid is faced with a choice when her old friends from Ghoul School show up.

added.title: Birdman
added.description: When Birdman makes the RV's attic his new home, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must figure out a way to make him leave before they're all driven crazy.

added.title: Pijamada Misteriosa
added.description: KO, Enid y Rad intentan resolver un misterio.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Fiesta de Monstruos
added.description: Enid debe tomar una decisión cuando llegan sus antiguos amigos de la Escuela de monstruos.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Princess Buttercup
added.description: When Buttercup starts spending a lot of time with her new friends, a group of bad-girl skaters called The Derbytantes, it seems the Powerpuff Girls are down to two, which delights Princess Morbucks, who wants to fill the empty slot.

added.title: Painbow
added.description: When a mysterious rainbow causes everyone to become unnaturally happy, the Powerpuff Girls must find where it ends to save the day and return Townsville to normal.

added.title: It Was Them
added.description: Dr. Animo has escaped his Plumber prison, and Ben and Rook must track him down before he turns the world into his personal mutant ant farm! (Introducing Nemetrix alien Slamworm, Galvan Plumbers Blukic and Driba, Arctiguana, new Ben alien Crashhopper.)

added.title: Dia de Nevada
added.description: Steven y las Gemas de Cristal tienen la oportunidad de ponerse al día en un día nevado.

added.title: Kevin 11
added.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

added.title: Porque tan triste?
added.description: Steven ha escuchado rumores de un par de Gemas que todavía están destruyendo mundos. Si él no puede detenerlas, tal vez Lapis sí.

added.title: Hot Stretch
added.description: Ben and Rook encounter a race of elastic, hot-blooded aliens in Undertown who want to use a stolen nuclear fusion engine to activate a volcano! (Introducing Ester, Seebik & the Kraaho.)

added.title: Last Laugh
added.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

added.title: Power Up Puff
added.description: During a fight, both Buttercup and Bubbles are surprised to discover they've leveled up, leaving Blossom to wonder when or if she'll get new powers too.

added.title: Dollar Hunt
added.description: Clarence hosts a fun "dollar hunt" game to meet new friends. But things go awry when Clarence accidentally buries the money his Mom gave him to buy refreshments for her book club meeting.

added.title: Lucky Girl
added.description: Ben battles an evil sorcerer whose power whose emanates from mystic charms, one of which turns Gwen into her own superhero named Lucky Girl.

added.title: Rise and Shine
added.description: A glimpse at the wild, secret adventures Clarence undertakes each day before the rest of us, and the sun, get up.

added.title: Man of the House
added.description: Clarence's first night home alone spirals out of control, forcing Clarence and his pals to wage war against their own home security measures.

added.title: Puddle Eyes
added.description: A nap in mud seals Clarence's eyes and leaves him sightless, potentially dooming his team's chances in the school's ill-conceived "Vision Bee."

added.title: Brain Game
added.description: Uncle Grandpa calls on Pizza Steve, the self-proclaimed master of video games, to help a kid beat a game.  Only problem: Pizza Steve is terrible at video games.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: Clarence struggles to make a connection at an all-girls slumber party, leaving Sumo and Jeff at odds without Clarence as their "friendship buffer."

added.title: Aluxes
added.description: Vic encuentra una antigua reliquia que invoca a una pandilla de traviesas criaturas, iy las consecuencias son desastrosas!

added.title: Punos Fuertes
added.description: Harto de perder cuando juega a los videojuegos contra su padre, Craig busca entrenarse en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Fiesta de Guillermo
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val se ven forzados a ir a la aburrida fiesta de cumpleaños de Guillermo, crean un plan para irse temprano, pero terminan descubriendo que la fiesta es mucho mejor de lo que pensaban.

added.title: Ninos de Globo
added.description: Vic y Val salen de viaje en globo aerostático con Sal y compiten por ser su favorito, pero las cosas se complican cuando tratan de usar las mágicas líneas de Nazca a su favor.

added.title: Carrera en el Arroyo
added.description: Una carrera de alta velocidad con un premio de alto riesgo puede ser demasiado para Craig y sus amigos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El Gran Robo de Bongos
added.description: Los chicos olvidan conseguir un regalo para Chata en el Día de la Abuela y en un movimiento desesperado, le regalan los bongos que pidieron prestados a Xochi. Sabiendo que deben devolver los tambores, Victor y Valentino fingen ser ladrones para robar los instrumentos.

added.title: Club de Lectura Secreto
added.description: Kelsey crea un club de lectura supersecreto para introducir a Craig y JP en las alegrías de la lectura.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Escape de Bahia Bebe
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic y Val se convierten a sí mismos y a Don en bebés, deben escapar de una guardería para poder volver a sus edades normales.

added.title: Poorbucks
added.description: When Morbucks loses her money, Blossom tries to reform her.

added.title: People Pleaser
added.description: Blossom neglects her promise to Bubbles when she takes on too many things leaving Buttercup and Bubbles to fend for themselves.

added.title: Big Trouble for Tiny Miracle
added.description: Tiny Miracle allows the gang to take advantage of his generosity at the expense of his own health.

added.title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad Ben World Part 1
added.description: Alternate dimensions, duplicate Bens and villains from throughout time and space! Just another day in Bellwood.

added.title: From Hedorium to Eternity
added.description: 11-year-old Ben, Gwen, and friends go on the adventure of a lifetime in their own backyard.

added.title: Let's Do the Time War Again
added.description: Ben, Skurd and Rook find themselves caught in an endless time loop as enemies from the future converge on Bellwood.

added.title: Ego - Egoista
added.description: Manzana y Cebolla tienen que demostrar que no son egoístas cuando hacen sus buenas acciones.

added.title: Salchichas y Dulce Golpe
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben superar sus obsesiones por las salchichas y los videojuegos.

added.title: La Explosion de Fuego Colosal
added.description: Cuando Colosal sale de un extraño estado de creatividad producto de una concentración extrema, es posible que haya hecho algo que podría destruir el Valle Puro Corazón entero.

added.title: El Ladron de Musica
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín tienen que defender la tienda de música del robo de instrumentos para conseguir una llave de la tienda.

added.title: Burlate con Todas tus Fuerzas
added.description: Cuando Adorabat empieza a interrumpir agresivamente a todos con su nuevo poder que le da energía, se convierte en una amenaza para el reino entero.

added.title: Entremedias
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín se pierden debajo de las tablas de madera del suelo y deben encontrar la salida.

added.title: La Mosca
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben deshacerse de una mosca que se metió en su apartamento o enfrentarse al desalojo.
